        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 4:03PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 403 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bessemer. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Birmingham, Hoover, Bessemer, Homewood, Hueytown,
Fairfield, Pleasant Grove, Midfield, Brighton, Lipscomb, Sylvan
Springs, Maytown, North Johns, Birmingham Fairgounds, Edgewater,
Bluff Park, Samford University, Splash Adventure, McDonald Chapel,
and Concord.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
